iAmmarTahir.name: iAmmarTahir/KnowledgeGraphGPT
iAmmarTahir.description: Transform plain text into a visually stunning Knowledge Graph with GPT-4 (latest preview)! It converts text into RDF tuples, and highlights the most frequent connections with a vibrant color-coding system. Download the results as a convenient JSON file for easy integration into your own projects.

iAmmarTahir.name: iAmmarTahir/MASK-RCNN-Dataset
iAmmarTahir.description: The Passport and ID Card Image Dataset is a collection of over 500 images of passports and ID cards, specifically created for the purpose of training RCNN models for image segmentation using Coco Annotator. The dataset includes high-quality images of passports and ID cards, covering a diverse range of countries, nationalities and designs.

iAmmarTahir.name: iAmmarTahir/Snake-Game
iAmmarTahir.description: This project is a classic Snake game written in x86 Assembly language, with over 1200 lines of code. The purpose of the project was to develop an understanding of how code is compiled into Assembly language and how Assembly language can be difficult and time-consuming to work with without high-level programming languages such as C++.

iAmmarTahir.name: iAmmarTahir/File-Access-System
iAmmarTahir.description: Its a basic implementation of lock table maintained by Database Management Systems (DBMS) in the backend using Hash Tables and Priority Queues.

iAmmarTahir.name: iAmmarTahir/community-detection
iAmmarTahir.description: Graph Neural Networks for Community Detection: A project leveraging GCNs and AGNNs to classify and detect subreddit communities in large social networks using the Reddit dataset.

iAmmarTahir.name: iAmmarTahir/Thulla-Engine
iAmmarTahir.description: Thulla Engine is a powerful multiplayer game engine built in Elixir that enables online players to play a popular card game from anywhere in the world. The game logic is handled through the use of Elixir's pattern matching, making the engine both efficient and reliable.

iAmmarTahir.name: iAmmarTahir/dup_file_remover
iAmmarTahir.description: A tool to find duplicate files in your File System

iAmmarTahir.description: A budgeting mobile app UI for Home makers.

iAmmarTahir.name: iAmmarTahir/essentials
iAmmarTahir.description: Essentials is a socially conscious e-commerce platform that aims to reduce food waste and mitigate global warming through the sale of surplus edible foods and fruits. The project won the Regional Finals out of over 850 projects in the Microsoft Imagine Cup 2020 competition, and was nominated for the National Finals.

iAmmarTahir.name: iAmmarTahir/page-book
iAmmarTahir.description: Pagebook is a cross-platform collaborative document editor designed for team collaboration. It is built using ReactJS and NodeJS, with real-time collaboration features powered by SocketIO. Teams across the world can work together on documents in real-time, ensuring seamless and efficient teamwork. Pagebook is an essential tool for modern-day teams

iiguelmamene.description: Designed and developed a program that gives turn-by-turn navigation from a start to finish location in the Westwood neighborhood of Los Angeles, California. Loads and indexes geospatial data from OpenStreetMap and implements the A* search algorithm to deliver optimal directions. C++.

iiguelmamene.name: iiguelmamene/disease-detector
iiguelmamene.description: Classifies whether a patient is suffering from heart disease, utilizing the UCI Heart Disease dataset. Cleans and filters data, identifying categorical and numerical features. Implements and tunes SVM, logistic regression, and KNN models. Evaluates effectiveness using recall score, achieving a best score of 0.83. Python.

iiguelmamene.name: iiguelmamene/taxi-ride-predictor
iiguelmamene.description: Predicts the travel time of a taxi ride in New York. Cleans, filters, and visualizes data. Implements various iterations of linear regression and neural network models. Reaches an RMSE of 193 seconds using a sequential neural network model with two hidden layers of 128 neurons each. Python, Keras, TensorFlow.

iiguelmamene.name: iiguelmamene/reddit-analysis
iiguelmamene.description: Worked with a team to engineer a program that analyzes Reddit comments from r/politics. Uses a binary CountVectorizer to turn comment data into a sparse feature vector for use by Spark machine learning features. Trains a logistic regression model to determine the sentiment of a particular r/politics comment. Python, Spark.  Contributors: Isaac Iguelmamene, Aadil Ali, Joey Ganley
